oud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7715-128030-3332-46/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-102922-662-76/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/115569229","headline":"BIO","description":"BIO:  from http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/MONFERRATO,%20SALUZZO,%20SAVONA.htm#AdelaidaVastodied1118 as of 2/6/2016\n\nMANFREDO (-1079).  \"Berta comitissa filia quondam Maginfredi et item Maginfredus et …","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthDate":"+1040","deathDate":"+1079","deathPlace":{"address":"Savona, Liguria, Italy","geo":{"latitude":44.3511,"longitude":8.4699,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Manfredo del Vasto, or Manfredi Incisa del Vasto ( Piedmont or Liguria, ... - Savona , 1079 ), brother of Bonifacio del Vasto Marquis of Savona and western Liguria, belonging to the Aleramici dynasty, was the father of Adelasia del Vasto, wife of the great Norman count Ruggero.\n\n\nhttps://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manfred_Ier_de_Saluces\n\n\n\n«b»Biography «/b»\nManfredo (or Manfredi), belonging to the Aleramici dynasty, son of the Marquis Teuto di Savona and Berta (daughter of Olderico Manfredi II, Marquis of Turin and Susa, and of Berta d'Este ) had four brothers, of whom he was probably the eldest: Bonifacio, Anselmo, Enrico and Otto, a cleric.\n\nHe was the father of Adelasia del Vasto, wife of the great Norman count Ruggero, and of Enrico del Vasto, head of the Aleramici of Sicily. He also had two daughters who married two illegitimate sons of the Norman count.\n\nManfredò died, with his brother Anselmo, a violent death in 1079 in Savona during a popular revolt. His brother Bonifacio became the tutor of the sons of Manfredo, who, within a few years, left their native lands to move to Sicily in the nascent kingdom of the Normans, where they acquired fiefs and possessions by relating to the Altavilla.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1040","date":"1040"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1064","date":"um 1064","place":"Istonio, Chieti, Abruzzo, Italy","age":"24","id":"G27F-6B7"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1064","date":"before 31 August 1064","place":"of Palermo, Cicily, Italy","age":"24","id":"G6M6-JXS"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1070","date":"about 1070","age":"30","id":"GNQV-WWC"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1070","date":"1070","place":"Italy","age":"30","id":"9CXW-2GL"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1075","date":"1075","place":"Sicily, Italy","age":"35","id":"99KK-LT6"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1079","date":"1079","place":"Savona, Liguria, Italy","age":"39"}],"parent":[{"name":"Marquis Tetone Oddone de Saluzzo di Savona II","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1035–1064","birthDate":"A+1035","deathDate":"/+1064-08-31","age":29,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/n21xl/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"G6M6-JXS","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G6M6-JXS/marquis-tetone-oddone-de-saluzzo-di-savona-ii-1035-1064","published":true},{"name":"Berta di Turino","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1022–1064","birthDate":"A+1022","deathDate":"A+1064","age":42,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/m21xl/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"G27F-6B7","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G27F-6B7/berta-di-turino-1022-1064","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Manfredo Del Vasto","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1040–1079","birthDate":"+1040","deathDate":"+1079","age":39,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/nrsml/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"LRCX-1VY","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LRCX-1VY/manfredo-del-vasto-1040-1079","published":true}],"sp